 <font color=#FF0000>(8/15/01 12:17:25 pm)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> <img src="http://www.steelwarrior.org/forum/p_exp.gif" align=absmiddle>  Re: What BP to use .. Barbed ringmail OR Fungi Tunic</span><hr size=1> On the surface, it looks like a no-brainer: the barbed ringmail coat has the fungi tunic beat hands down for what matters to a warrior: AC and HP's...the +9 STR is nice too. The gungi tunic loses 10 from DEX and AGI, which translates to even lower AC and less chances to proc your weapons...<br>
<br>
...but the fungi tunic has that regen going for it...<br>
<br>
...but in the end it's going to depend on your style of play. If you solo or are in small two/three person groups without a cleric, the fungi tunic is worth a look. If your group consistently has a cleric and either a druid or shammie, the fungi is pretty much useless. Regen is not going to save your butt in a fight when mobs are hitting you for 100+ a pop, but the added AC from the ringmail coat might.<br>
<br>
The total AC difference between the two is pretty severe (btw, I'm using raw item AC×1.55 as the formula...only one I found): The ringmail coat is 30 AC, which will translate to about 46 AC in the end. The fungi tunic is 21 AC, and with that -10 AGI the final AC you'll get from it is around 29...net difference: 17 AC in favor of the ringmail coat.<br>
<br>
If your play style allows it, I'd sell the fungi tunic...the price has come down pretty considerably in the last few weeks, so it's best to get out while the gettin's hot, and get yourself some nice armor upgrades with the pp.<br>
<br>
Just an opinion...<br>
<br>
